ResourceHeader.Description: Wave Normal Analysis products, based on L1 spectral matrix survey E and B data, and produced via PRASSADCO (Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003). A correction for antenna sheath effects has been applied to the electric field data, before being input to PRASSADCO. The correction is density-dependent, so fill values are inserted for E-dependent data where a density estimate is not available. Be aware that the spin-plane E antennas began deployment at 2012-09-13T23:06, and were not fully deployed until 2012-09-22T22:32. The spin-axis deployment began on 2012-09-24T20:33 and did not fully complete until 2012-12-07T17:25. Noise levels in the E data are increased by incomplete antenna deployment. There was a significant upgrade to the onboard calibration tables, for both E and B in Feb 2013. Prior to this, the highest survey frequency bin (11.24 kHz) used a flawed cal value that resulted in both amplitude and phase errors. The effect is stronger for the B data. New, corrected, tables took effect at 2013-02-13T01:48:00. In Mar 2013, there was a ~2-day interval where a software issue resulted in the wrong calibration tables being used for both E and B data. These data should be used with extreme caution. The interval is 2013-03-21T09:35:00 to 2013-03-23T02:07:00.

Parameter.Name: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Epoch
Parameter.Caveats: Epoch at midpoint of the 0.468 second sampling interval for survey data.

Parameter.Name: WFR_frequencies
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: WFR_frequencies
Parameter.Caveats: Average frequency of the set of FFT frequencies that were combined when creating the frequency bins for the spectral matrix data.

Parameter.Name: b3
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Power Spectral Density of B!bparallel!n
Parameter.Caveats: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

Parameter.Name: bsum
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Sum of the Three Magnetic Power Spectral Densities

Parameter.Name: bsumperp
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Sum of Two Perpendicular Magnetic Power Spectral Densities
Parameter.Caveats: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Perpendicular components are along axis1 (outward) and axis2 (eastward).

Parameter.Name: cohb1_2
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Coherence Between B!bperp1!n and B!bperp2!n
Parameter.Caveats: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

Parameter.Name: cohb1_3
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Coherence Between B!bperp1!n and B!bpar!n
Parameter.Caveats: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

Parameter.Name: cohb2_3
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Coherence Between B!bperp2!n and B!bpar!n
Parameter.Caveats: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

Parameter.Name: ez
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Power Spectral Density of E!bparallel!n
Parameter.Caveats: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with Z along B0, X outward from the Earth, and Y eastward.

Parameter.Name: ezf
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Power Spectral Density of E!bparallel!n Using Faraday Law
Parameter.Caveats: Does not use measured spin-axis E data when calculating E components in field-aligned system. Spin-axis E is synthesized from the two spin-plane E and all three B components, using Faraday law and plane-wave assumption (Sec. 3.3, Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003). Coordinate system is field-aligned, with Z along B0, X outward from the Earth, and Y eastward.

Parameter.Name: esum
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Sum of the Three Electric Power Spectral Densities

Parameter.Name: esumperp
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Sum of Two Perpendicular Electric Power Spectral Densities
Parameter.Caveats: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Perpendicular components are along axis1 (outward) and along axis2 (eastward).

Parameter.Name: esumperpf
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Sum of Two Perpendicular Electric Power Spectral Densities Using Faraday Law
Parameter.Caveats: Does not use measured spin-axis E data when calculating E components in field-aligned system. Spin-axis E is synthesized from the two spin-plane E and all three B components, using Faraday law and plane-wave assumption (Sec. 3.3, Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003). Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Perpendicular components are along axis1 (outward) and along axis2 (eastward).

Parameter.Name: eigen
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Degree of Polarization of The Magnetic Field From Eigenvalues
Parameter.Caveats: Eigenvalues are determined using the SVD method (Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003)

Parameter.Name: ellsvd
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Ellipticity of the Magnetic Field Polarization
Parameter.Caveats: Determined using the SVD method, from eq. 13 of Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003

Parameter.Name: polsvd
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Degree of Magnetic Field Polarization in the Polarization Plane
Parameter.Caveats: Determined using the SVD method, from eq. A6 in the appendix of Santolik, et al., J. Geophys. Res., 107(A12), 1444, 2002.

Parameter.Name: plansvd
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Planarity of the Magnetic Field Polarization
Parameter.Caveats: Determined using the SVD method, from eq. 12 of Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003.

Parameter.Name: plansvde
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Electromagnetic Planarity
Parameter.Caveats: Electromagnetic planarity calculated from the 6x6 spectral matrix using eq. 24 of Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003.

Parameter.Name: thsvd
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Polar Angle of the Wave Vector
Parameter.Caveats: Wave Normal Angles are determined using the SVD method (Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003). Angle is measured from axis3, but all angles are 0 <= theta <= 90, due to ambiguity in the SVN method. Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0.

Parameter.Name: phsvd
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Azimuthal Angle of the Wave Vector
Parameter.Caveats: Wave Normal Angles are determined using the SVD method (Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003). Angle is measured counterclockwise from axis1. Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

Parameter.Name: poy1_2_3
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Spectral Density of the Poynting Flux
Parameter.Caveats: Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

Parameter.Name: thpoy1_2_3
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Polar Angle of the Poynting Vector
Parameter.Caveats: Angle is measured from axis3. Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

Parameter.Name: phpoy1_2_3
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Azimuthal Angle of the Poynting Vector
Parameter.Caveats: Angle is measured counterclockwise from axis1. Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

Parameter.Name: poyf1_2_3
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Spectral Density of the Poynting Flux Using Faraday Law
Parameter.Caveats: Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Does not use measured spin-axis E data when calculating E components in field-aligned system. Spin-axis E is synthesized from the two spin-plane E and all three B components, using Faraday law and plane-wave assumption (Sec. 3.3, Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003).

Parameter.Name: thpoyf1_2_3
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Polar Angle of the Poynting Vector Using Faraday Law
Parameter.Caveats: Angle is measured from axis3. Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Does not use measured spin-axis E data when calculating E components in field-aligned system. Spin-axis E is synthesized from the two spin-plane E and all three B components, using Faraday law and plane-wave assumption (Sec. 3.3, Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003).

Parameter.Description: Azimuthal Angle of the Poynting Vector Using Faraday Law
Parameter.Caveats: Angle is measured counterclockwise from axis1. Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Does not use measured spin-axis E data when calculating E components in field-aligned system. Spin-axis E is synthesized from the two spin-plane E and all three B components, using Faraday law and plane-wave assumption (Sec. 3.3, Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003).

Parameter.Name: Tuvw2fac
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Transformation Matrix, Antenna-Frame->Field-Aligned Coordinates
Parameter.Caveats: If V is a vector field value in the antenna frame [u, v, w], then Tuvw2fac ## V is that same quantity in the field-aligned coordinate system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward

Parameter.Name: Buvw
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Buvw, nT
Parameter.Caveats: The 3-vector B field from the EMFISIS MAG instrument in the spacecraft antenna coordinate system, with axis3 (w) along the spin-axis, axis1 (u) and axis2 (v) in the spin plane. Value is a linear interpolation between the two nearest (in time) magnetometer measurements to the specific epochs in this CDF.

Parameter.Name: EclipseFlag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Flag Indicating Spacecraft in Eclipse
Parameter.Caveats: Value of 1 for a record indicates that spacecraft was in eclipse at the epoch of that record.

Parameter.Name: ThrusterFlag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Flag Indicating Thruster Firing
Parameter.Caveats: Value of 1 for a record indicates that spacecraft thrusters were firing at the epoch of that record.

Parameter.Name: ChargeEvtFlag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Flag Indicating Spacecraft Charging Event
Parameter.Caveats: Value of 1 for a record indicates that there was a spacecraft charging event at the epoch of that record. A charging event is defined as when the average of either pair of spin-plane EFW probes ((V1+V2)/2 or (V3+V4)/2) is > 2 V. Use caution interpreting electric field data during such an event.

Parameter.Name: SunShadowFlag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Flag Indicating Anti-sunward Ew Antenna is Shadowed
Parameter.Caveats: Value of 1 for a record indicates that the anti-sunward E antenna (probe 5) was shadowed by some other part of the spacecraft within 0.4 second of the epoch of that record.

Parameter.Name: Density
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Interpolated density
Parameter.Caveats: Density value used when calculating the sheath corrections to E data. Based on densities derived from the upper-hybrid resonance line, but interpolated to the specific epochs in this CDF. Will be Fill when no density value is available. See rbsp-b_density_emfisis-L4_*.cdf files for the source densities.

Parameter.Name: EuSheathCorMag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Magnitude of Sheath Correction for Eu
Parameter.Caveats: Magnitude of the sheath correction applied to the Eu antenna spectral density data. Raw data are effectively multiplied by this number to produce corrected data (actual magnitude and phase corrections are applied in a single operation in the complex domain). Coordinate system is the spacecraft antenna system, with axis3 (w) along the spin-axis, axis1 (u) and axis2 (v) in the spin plane. Fill values indicate that no correction was applied.

Parameter.Name: EuSheathCorPhase
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Phase of Sheath Correction for Eu
Parameter.Caveats: Complex phase of the sheath correction applied to the Eu antenna spectral density data. Raw data effectively have this number added to their complex phase to produce corrected data (actual magnitude and phase corrections are applied in a single operation in the complex domain). Coordinate system is the spacecraft antenna system, with axis3 (w) along the spin-axis, axis1 (u) and axis2 (v) in the spin plane. Fill values indicate that no correction was applied.
